{
  "query": "What is the evidence for managing linear features like hedges and riparian buffers on farmland to benefit bats?",
  "relevant_summary": "The evidence for managing linear features like hedges and riparian buffers on farmland to benefit bats is limited and mixed. One replicated, paired sites study in the UK found that pipistrelle activity (relative abundance) did not differ along waterways with riparian buffers on agri-environment scheme farms compared to conventional farms (action ID 2284). Similarly, one replicated, paired sites study in the UK found that pipistrelle activity did not differ between hedges managed for wildlife on agri-environment scheme farms and hedges on conventional farms (action ID 1943). However, one replicated, site comparison study in the UK found that hedges trimmed \u22653 years prior had more bat species recorded along them than hedges trimmed during the previous winter, and higher activity of two of eight bat species/species groups (action ID 1943).",
